HEADWORD: Intrinsically
<hw>In*trin"sic*al*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<def>Internally; in its nature; essentially; really; truly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A lie is a thing absolutely and <qex>intrinsically</qex> evil.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intrinsicalness</ent>⟦br⟧
